19
00:01:15,780 --> 00:01:17,560
But let's look at this word, "light".

20
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:23,439
You could translate it to "la luz" as in "light from sunlight" or "light from a light bulb".

21
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:27,700
And you could also translate this to "ligera" as in "light as a feather".

22
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,520
And as you saw earlier, "llamas" can be translated to "flames" as in "flames at a campfire".

23
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:38,360
Or it could also be translated to "llamas" the cute animals with long necks.

24
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:44,940
Or "llamas" can be part of this phrase "como te llamas" where "llamas" means "to call oneself".

25
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:51,279
So "como te llamas" is Spanish for "what is your name?"

26
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:54,060
So there are some words that look the same and sound the same.

27
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:55,200
Here's one more example.

28
00:01:55,500 --> 00:02:00,420
The word "bank" in English could be translated to "banco" as in a financial institution

29
