30
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:06,260
It could also be translated to "orilla" which is the land next to a river.

31
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:11,220
And to make things even more fun, the Spanish word for "banco" can be a bank where you

32
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:14,680
deposit your money, but can also be a bench that you sit on at a park.

33
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:21,480
These words, light, llamas, bank, banco, are examples of two or more distinct words with

34
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:25,920
their own distinct meanings that happen to look the same and also sound the same.

35
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:31,160
If two distinct words have the same spelling and pronunciation, they're called homonyms.

36
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:35,740
There are also words that look the same but don't necessarily sound the same.

37
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:41,759
